   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>To his friend and neighbour Maister IOHN TAYLOR.</head>
   <l>FIerce <hi>Neptunes</hi> wrath, and <hi>Eol's</hi> angry spleene</l>
   <l>Full many a time I haue both felt and seene,</l>
   <l>In leaking ship, and which hath grieu'd me more,</l>
   <l>In a long night a darke Moone, and lee shore:</l>
   <l>But such a storme as thou describest h<gap reason="illegible: missing" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ere,</l>
   <l>Amazeth mee with wonder and with feare</l>
   <l>And wert thou not both Water-man and Poet</l>
   <l>Thou neuer couldest halfe so plainely show it,</l>
   <l>I much reioyce thou safe on shore art come,</l>
   <l>And bid thee very kindly welcome home.</l>
   <byline>Thomas Smith.</byline>
